          <h1>Dry Skin Acne Treatment</h1>
          <p>Usually people think that acne is found only on oily skin. But there are many people with dry skin and still suffering from acne. If you take notice, you can see many people having dry skin and acne. It is somewhat difficult to treat acne on dry skin. Most of the products that you get in the market are made for treating acne on oily skin. Using such products on the skin will make your skin all the more dry. So, if you have dry skin acne, here is the solution for you.</p>
          <h3>Dry Skin Acne Treatment Tips:</h3>
          <p>These remedies take proper care of your dry skin and at the same time helps in getting rid of acne.</p>
          <h4>Always keep your skin safe from wind, sun, cold and other such elements:</h4>
          <p>If you ever think of going out on a windy and cold day, take are not to expose your skin to the harsh cold and the drying effects of wind. Put on a hat or a scarf to protect your skin from getting dried by wind and the cold. Similarly, when you go out in the sun, use a good sun screen lotion. You can use nonacnegenic or noncomedogenic sunscreen to save your skin from getting affected by the rays of the sun.</p>
          <h4>Choose your cleanser well:</h4>
          <p>You have to be very careful in choosing the right cleanser for your skin. Like the moisturizers made for acne-prone skin, cleansers made for such purpose can also make your skin very dry. Cleansers that do not foam when applied on the skin are the best option for dry skin. These keep your skin from getting dry. Always use a non-medicated cleanser when you are using a topical medicated ointment, lotion or cream for treating acne. If you are thinking of using a medicated cleanser, you must first take the advice of a skin specialist and then use it.</p>
          <h4>Do not over wash:</h4>
          <p>If you wash your skin too often, the skin may lose its natural oils and moisture and this leads to drier skin. So do not over wash your skin. If you are using a cleanser to clean your face, use it only once a day. You can use it in the evening after removing all the makeup from your face. Just a few splashes of water is enough to remove the dirt from your skin. By doing so, you can get the skin cleaned and at the same time prevent it from getting more dry.</p>
          <h4>Moisturize regularly:</h4>
          <p>When you have a dry skin, you have to keep it well moisturized to prevent it from getting dry. You may think how it is possible to prevent acne breakout if you keep your skin moisturized. The answer is very simple. Use the correct moisturizer. You can use moisturizers specially made for sensitive skin. They are light and very effective on dry skin. If you use moisturizers that are made for acne prone skin, your skin will get even drier. So never use such moisturizers.</p>
          <h4>Use lotions and creams to treat acne:</h4>
          <p>Most of the products for acne removal that you can buy from the market are those which dry your skin. . But when you have a dry skin, you may use less drying products like creams, lotions and ointments. These keep your skin from getting dry and help to remove acne.  One thing to remember when using these products is not to apply it more than that is mentioned on it. You may think that using it in excess will help in removing the acne faster and makes your skin better. But this is a wrong conception. So use it as directed and no more than that.</p>
