          <h3>Home Remedies for Acne on Dry Skin:</h3>
          <h4>Cucumber:</h4>
          <p>Cucumber is great for your skin and provides you a clear and bright skin. It helps in giving coolness to your skin and also prevents skin irritation. Grind a cucumber and apply on the face. This will moisturize your skin and also removes excess oil from the skin. Regular use of this vegetable keeps your skin moisturized and blemish free.</p>
          <h4>Garlic:</h4>
          <p>Garlic is a good source of zinc, sulphur, allicin and calcium, all of which have antifungal and antibacterial properties. Make a paste of garlic and cloves with a little water and apply on your face. Wash off after a few minutes.</p>
          <h4>Lemon juice:</h4>
          <p>The acidic nature of lemon helps in drying up of acne on the skin. Dip cotton balls in fresh lemon juice and apply on the affected area. This gives you a clear skin.</p>
          <h4>Potato:</h4>
          <p>Due to the presence of vitamin C in potato, the production of collagen in the skin is increased by applying potato on the face. Grate a potato and apply it as a face pack. This also heals as well as prevents any harm caused by the rays of the sun. Regeneration of the skin is promoted by the presence of vitamin B in this vegetable, while niacin present in it has skin lightening properties.</p>
          <h4>Tomato pulp:</h4>
          <p>Tomato is a rich source of vitamins A, C and K, which are found in most of the lotions and creams that you get in the market for the treatment of acne. Moreover, it also has acidic properties, which leads to the drying up of acne on the skin. All you have to do is to cut a tomato and scrub your face with the tomato piece. You can also mash one tomato and apply it on the face as a face pack. Wait for a few minutes and then wash off. Apply this regularly for a few weeks till the acne disappear.</p>
          <p>So, try some of the tips given above and stay cool with an acne free skin that is well moisturized and glowing.</p>
